 <!--75-->Goblin Scimitar x4<br />
 <!--955-->The Balrog&#39;s Sword<br />
 <!--975-->Power and Terror    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Fellowship Strategy<br />
<br />
 The Fellowship exploits Aragorn&#39;s Exert to Heal ability and Boromir&#39;s add Twilight to Heal ability to heal archers every turn. With Shoulder to Shoulder, Galadriels High Vitality and Citadel of Minas Tirth you have an obscene amount of healing. For players who wish more healing change Elrond, Lord of Rivendell for Elrond, Hearld of Gil-Galad. The fellowship survives by using archery from your elves with bows, Aragorn, Legolas and Galadriel when you get Splendour of their Banners on her. While your highest strength minions clean up the popcorn. Eowyn is in their for players with one tough minion and a bunch of popcorn.<br />
<br />
Shadow Strategy<br />
<br />
 The Shadow side attempts to Swarm over and over again but this is a decoy. You are really setting up for a site 9 Swarm. It utilizes Goblin Swarms for replaying minions, Gimli, Dwarf of Erebor for sending your Balrog related cards to the bottom of your deck and Goblin Sneak to put your runners or other 1 twilight minions on the bottom. It uses Power and Terror to play the Balrog dirt cheap with his sword. While Fill with Fear screws over Archery Decks and Dark Places not only pumps the Balrog but makes sure site 9 is underground.<br />
<br />
I hope you enjoy the deck<br />
              Zak Cardwell          <br />
